## MEDIUM — Appeal system backend + admin controls for verification tuning

### What's wrong
Users who get marginal/rejected verdicts need a way to appeal. Admins need to view verification stats and tune thresholds without redeploying.

### What to build

#### 1. Appeal API routes

Add to `photos.ts` or create `backend/node-services/api-server/src/routes/appeals.ts`:

**POST /api/v1/photos/appeals** (authenticated)
```typescript
// Body: { verificationId: number, reason?: string }
// Validations:
//   - verificationId must exist and belong to this user
//   - Max 1 pending appeal per verification
//   - Max 3 appeals per day per user (rate limit)
//   - Reason max 500 chars
// Response: { success: true, data: { id, status: 'pending', createdAt } }
```

**GET /api/v1/photos/appeals/mine** (authenticated)
```typescript
// Returns user's appeals with verification context
// Response: { success: true, data: { appeals: [{ id, verificationId, reason, status, createdAt, verdict, score }] } }
// Join with photo_verifications to include verdict/score
```

**PATCH /api/v1/admin/appeals/:id** (admin only)
```typescript
// Body: { status: 'approved' | 'denied' }
// On 'approved':
//   1. Update appeal status + reviewed_by + reviewed_at
//   2. Update photo_verifications.verdict → 'accepted'
//   3. Award missing XP: if was marginal (got 40), award remaining 40. If was rejected (got 0), award 80.
//   4. Update user_trust_tiers (increment verified_count)
//   5. Recalculate progression unlocks for the skill
// On 'denied':
//   1. Update appeal status only
// Response: { success: true, data: { id, status, reviewedAt } }
```

#### 2. Admin verification stats endpoint

**GET /api/v1/admin/verification-stats** (admin only)
```typescript
// Response:
{
  success: true,
  data: {
    totalVerified: number,
    verdictBreakdown: { accepted: number, marginal: number, rejected: number },
    avgScore: number,
    avgProcessingMs: number,
    signalPassRates: Record<string, number>, // e.g. { color_diversity: 0.82, ... }
    appealStats: { pending: number, approved: number, denied: number },
    trustTierDistribution: { new: number, trusted: number, veteran: number },
  }
}
```

SQL for signal pass rates:
```sql
SELECT
  AVG(CASE WHEN color_diversity >= 0.4 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS color_diversity_rate,
  AVG(CASE WHEN saturation_warmth >= 0.35 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS saturation_warmth_rate,
  -- ... repeat for all signals
  AVG(total_score) AS avg_score,
  AVG(processing_ms) AS avg_processing_ms,
  COUNT(*) AS total
FROM photo_verifications;
```

